The paper deals with the problem of autonomous driving, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The method proposed in the paper uses deep convolutional networks to predict trajectories, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also addresses the issue of uncertainty and the need for anticipating multiple possible behaviors, which is a key challenge in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
